==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unspeakable
<hw>Unspeakable</hw> <def>See <er>speakable</er>.</def>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unspeakable
<hw>Un*speak"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>speakable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not speakable;
incapable of being uttered or adequately described; inexpressible;
unutterable; ineffable; <as>as, <ex>unspeakable</ex> grief or
rage</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Un*speak"a*bly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye rejoice with joy <qex>unspeakable</qex> and full of glory.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Pet. i. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unspecialized</ent>⟦br⟧
